title: For Sale:  Early 80's Daisy Trail Rider in Package Toy Gun
postcontent: This is a vintage Daisy Trail Rider #660 that was given to me as a kid, but I never played with it.  Its been moving from closet to closet for 30+ years, and it is time for it to find a new home!I can't tell you alot about this other than it still works and makes it's ricochet sound.  As for dating the gun, it has a gold plastic insert and not the orange plastic insert that was used 1988 and later because of Federal law.  So it is pre-1988.  Also, the back refers to Daisy being a Kiddie Inc. company.  They were not called Kiddie Inc. until 1980.  So this is somwhere between 1980-1988.  I was told that the Western Auto in Mt Sterling went out of business in 1985, and I assume it came from that one.  This would narrow it down to between 1980-1985.As for what this is worth, I have no idea.  If I've priced it too cheap then someone will jump on it.  If it is too high, make me a decent offer and we will see where it goes.  AT auction, I have seen these in decent working condition sell for $20-$25 for the gun with no packaging.  So I guess it is a matter of what the packaging adds.Cash only.  No trades.  Can meet in Fleming County or surrounding area (Bath, Rowan, Mason, Montgomery, etc.).  I might even be able to dip into Ohio (Aberdeen, Ripley, etc.) on this one.  No haggling over price when meeting to conduct the transaction.  We will agree on price in advance and you will be able to inspect the item to make sure it is suitable and conduct the transaction.  Since this is a toy, no restrictions on who can purchase.  However, no shipping just because the gun is so long, it is very difficult to package without outrageous shipping charges.

title: For Sale:  Citadel Full Size 1911 - Brand New
postcontent:
For sale is a brand new, unfired in box Citadel 1911A1-45FS Semiautomatic Pistol in .45 ACP caliber. The Citadel pistols are the upscale version of the Rock Island Armory pistols made by Armscor that come with a better finish, nicer grips, and normally two magazines instead of just one that comes with the RIA guns.
This is a full-featured tactical pistol which is ready for general shooting, home defense, or club-level competition. It has combat sights, ambidexterous thumb safeties, and a match grade adjustable trigger that measures 4.5 pounds on this gun. The slide features front and rear cocking serrations, and the entire gun is finished in a non-glare matte finish with some really nice checkered wood grips.
Once again, this is a brand new pistol which has never been fired, and comes with a full manufacturer's lifetime warranty. It includes the box and papers, the origiinal fired shell casing where it was test fired at the factory, and a total of 2 ACT 8-round magazines. The two nickel finished additional magazines shown in the photo are no longer available and not included, and I have lowered the price of the gun to reflect this. This package will make a great entry into the world of the 1911 and the .45 ACP cartridge if you are ready for something different than your typical 9mm plastic pistol.
I bought two of these pistols from the distributor and decided to keep one, so this one is for sale. I'm primarily interested in selling for cash, but will listen to any trades you would like to discuss. Buyer must have a Florida Driver's License, a Concealed Handgun Permit, and be legally able to own a firearm in Florida. I will provide a Bill of Sale. Transaction will take place at my office in Homestead, no exceptions. This is not me being a jerk, I am disabled and cannot easily travel. Face to face transactions only. Price is $525.00 or best offer.
Thanks for looking at my listing.

title: For Sale:  TROY Pump Action Rifle .300 AAC BLACKOUT 16" SPAR-
postcontent: If you are one of the unlucky few gun enthusiasts who lives in a state with draconian and unconstitutional firearms laws, odds are you may well be aware of the Troy Sporting Rifle, or Pump Action Rifle (PAR). Troy, a company that knows its way around fighting black rifles, has answered the call for a fully functional MSR that delivers uncompromising performance and accuracy, and they’ve packaged it in a form that most of us know and respect. The PAR remains true to its AR-15 roots, and it is 50 state legal.Before we get too far in, let’s clear up some confusion. Some early press and comments on this gun implied, mistakenly, that this was simply a pump action AR-15. PAR stands for pump action rifle–not pump AR-15. It is an honest mistake, I think, and one I caught myself making, at least causally. The Troy Sporting Rifle is not, despite the visual similarities, an AR-15. The Troy Sporting Rifle is clearly a branch on the AR family tree—but AR means ArmaLite Rifle, and this, dear readers, is a Troy. Even if you were to use the relaxed nomenclature associated with the abbreviation AR, (like automatic rifle, or–worse–assault rifle,) you’d still be off. This is a pump gun meant for sporting purposes. The upper and lower of the PAR are not interchangeable with those of the AR-15; ergo, this is not an AR. This is, however, a truly fine example of a modern sporting rifle. And it will be instantly familiar to those of you who know your way around black semi-automatic modular “assault” rifles built in the style of ArmaLite and hundreds of others.
